"But one day, out of the blue, one of the project leaders dropped me an email with photos and said, “Look, here’s your mini brain.” And there it was ... I wish there was some drama to it, but the researchers were pretty casual about it because they grow these things all the time. And I wish I could say that I remember thinking, “Oh my God, this is my second brain,” but I think I was more relieved than anything that it actually grew into an organoid. The fact that they actually got one that had these really clear, discernible structures in it was pretty remarkable. If anything, I felt a little bit proud of myself that we actually created something in the end.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"value":"For me, one of the really interesting things I gleaned from the project was that the stuff we are made from is incredibly versatile. The technology of transforming cells from virtually any other tissue in the body is relatively new, and it’s leading to all sorts of directions in medicine and research. I was fascinated to see firsthand what extraordinary things cells — even mature, adult cells — are capable of. ","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"document"}},"related":[{"image":{"description":"Maria Korneeva/Moment via Getty Images","id":"2xlwdcoHFitFooAWIYUYto","title":"file-20240424-22-kj3kp7","url":"//images.ctfassets.net/cnu0m8re1exe/2xlwdcoHFitFooAWIYUYto/df3ad9e0478a8ac0dfe180dfbaa7ce40/file-20240424-22-kj3kp7.jpg"},"refs":{"category":{"image":{},"sortOrder":1,"name":"Mind","id":"7De5hhPGZgflHOPHejferZ","hideRightRail":false,"slug":"mind"},"tags":[{"image":{},"name":"emotions","id":"4OHPWgoFmW1jHCBU7cv68i","hideRightRail":false,"slug":"emotions"},{"image":{},"name":"brain structure \u0026 function","id":"6kjg8IL7cdHL9ybux3GgOA","hideRightRail":false,"slug":"brain-structure-function"},{"image":{},"name":"brain","id":"6FbYDWzhcfmEWRHBIr2WVu","hideRightRail":false,"slug":"br